15#ifndef ISC_SYMTAB_H
16#define ISC_SYMTAB_H 1
17
18/*****
19 ***** Module Info
20 *****/
21
22/*! \file isc/symtab.h
23 * \brief Provides a simple memory-based symbol table.
24 *
25 * Keys are C strings, and key comparisons are case-insensitive. A type may
26 * be specified when looking up, defining, or undefining. A type value of
27 * 0 means "match any type"; any other value will only match the given
28 * type.
29 *
30 * It's possible that a client will attempt to define a <key, type, value>
31 * tuple when a tuple with the given key and type already exists in the table.
32 * What to do in this case is specified by the client. Possible policies are:
33 *
34 *\li #isc_symexists_reject Disallow the define, returning #ISC_R_EXISTS
35 *\li #isc_symexists_replace Replace the old value with the new. The
36 * undefine action (if provided) will be called
37 * with the old <key, type, value> tuple.
38 *\li #isc_symexists_add Add the new tuple, leaving the old tuple in
39 * the table. Subsequent lookups will retrieve
40 * the most-recently-defined tuple.
41 *
42 * A lookup of a key using type 0 will return the most-recently defined
43 * symbol with that key. An undefine of a key using type 0 will undefine the
44 * most-recently defined symbol with that key. Trying to define a key with
45 * type 0 is illegal.
46 *
47 * The symbol table library does not make a copy the key field, so the
48 * caller must ensure that any key it passes to isc_symtab_define() will not
49 * change until it calls isc_symtab_undefine() or isc_symtab_destroy().
50 *
51 * A user-specified action will be called (if provided) when a symbol is
52 * undefined. It can be used to free memory associated with keys and/or
53 * values.
54 *
55 * A symbol table is implemented as a hash table of lists; the size of the
56 * hash table is set by the 'size' parameter to isc_symtbl_create(). When
57 * the number of entries in the symbol table reaches three quarters of this
58 * value, the hash table is reallocated with size doubled, in order to
59 * optimize lookup performance. This has a negative effect on insertion
60 * performance, which can be mitigated by sizing the table appropriately
61 * when creating it.
62 *
63 * \li MP:
64 * The callers of this module must ensure any required synchronization.
65 *
66 * \li Reliability:
67 * No anticipated impact.
68 *
69 * \li Resources:
70 * TBS
71 *
72 * \li Security:
73 * No anticipated impact.
74 *
75 * \li Standards:
76 * None.
77 */
78
79/***
80 *** Imports.
81 ***/
82
83#include <stdbool.h>
84
85#include <isc/lang.h>
86#include <isc/types.h>
87
88/*
89 *** Symbol Tables.
90 ***/
91/*% Symbol table value. */
92typedef union isc_symvalue {
93 void * as_pointer;
94 const void * as_cpointer;
95 int as_integer;
96 unsigned int as_uinteger;
97} isc_symvalue_t;
98
99typedef void (*isc_symtabaction_t)(char *key, unsigned int type,
100 isc_symvalue_t value, void *userarg);
101/*% Symbol table exists. */
102typedef enum {
103 isc_symexists_reject = 0, /*%< Disallow the define */
104 isc_symexists_replace = 1, /*%< Replace the old value with the new */
105 isc_symexists_add = 2 /*%< Add the new tuple */
106} isc_symexists_t;
107
108ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
109
110/*% Create a symbol table. */
111isc_result_t
112isc_symtab_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, unsigned int size,
113 isc_symtabaction_t undefine_action, void *undefine_arg,
114 bool case_sensitive, isc_symtab_t **symtabp);
115
116/*% Destroy a symbol table. */
117void
118isc_symtab_destroy(isc_symtab_t **symtabp);
119
120/*% Lookup a symbol table. */
121isc_result_t
122isc_symtab_lookup(isc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type,
123 isc_symvalue_t *value);
124
125/*% Define a symbol table. */
126isc_result_t
127isc_symtab_define(isc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type,
128 isc_symvalue_t value, isc_symexists_t exists_policy);
129
130/*% Undefine a symbol table. */
131isc_result_t
132isc_symtab_undefine(isc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type);
133
134/*% Return the number of items in a symbol table. */
135unsigned int
136isc_symtab_count(isc_symtab_t *symtab);
137ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
138
139#endif /* ISC_SYMTAB_H */
